se, complete agreement. Verify the merge output is lossless and properly formatted.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior requires multiple agentic steps (three independent LLM-based reviewers) coordinated together in sequence/parallel. Testing only individual reviewers (Agentic) would miss coordination failures: dispatch errors, timeout/partial result collection, merge failures that compound across multiple reviewers. The end-to-end risk is at the workflow level—can the system reliably orchestrate three LLM calls, collect their results, and merge them losslessly? This requires real LLM calls to all three reviewers to validate the full pipeline works together.","test_description":"Test the full pipeline with a real contract that is complex enough to produce distinct findings from each reviewer. Verify: (1) all three reviewers are successfully dispatched (concurrently or sequentially per design), (2) all three complete and results are collected without timeout or partial failure, (3) every finding from every reviewer appears in the final merged report, (4) no findings are dropped, duplicated, or corrupted during the merge. Measure latency and resource usage to ensure parallel dispatch does not introduce bottlenecks. Test with contracts of varying complexity and size. Verify the unified report is complete and correctly attributed.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.7}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13369,"cache_read_input_tokens